lisa-design:
- Data fetching uses the shared useAuthenticatedInstance() axios directly (instance.get), NOT useDataApi. Rationale: lazy per-key children fetches can't cleanly reuse a single useDataApi execute()/data ref; the raw instance still gives baseURL + auth + the camelCase response interceptor. Cache is a module-level Map keyed by scope+parentKey and shared across tree/graph/widget.
- Fixture fallback is intentional and dual-mode (spec: "demoable either way"): useLineage serves fixtures when forced (env VITE_LINEAGE_FIXTURES=true | ?fixtures=1 | localStorage lineageFixtures=1) AND auto-falls back to fixtures on any API request error. `usingFixtures` ref drives a visible "demo data" banner in both views. Do not "fix" the catch-all fallback into a hard error — it keeps the PoC demoable with the API down.
- Edge kind is DERIVED, not carried by the API node: child.nodeType starting with "procedure" => 'documents' (dashed/de-emphasised), else 'implements' (solid). If the API later adds an explicit edge field, prefer it over this heuristic.
- Graph dedups DAG nodes by `key` (Map) so a shared policy node renders ONCE with multiple inbound edges; the tree intentionally renders the same node twice (once per parent) per the spec.
- heatScale.ts is the single source of heat colour. ABSOLUTE buckets (0=neutral, 1-9=yellow, 10-24=amber, 25-49=orange, >=50=red). Class strings are COMPLETE literals (Tailwind JIT requirement) and carry dark: variants so colours survive dark mode. Non-finite/<=0 => neutral (Infinity => neutral, by design).
- Drawer evidence is best-effort and `[PoC corner]`: skipped under fixtures or when the node has no controlId. Primary drawer content (both scores, compliance breakdown, linkage chips, risk-by-status with accepted/mitigated muted) is derived from node data so it always renders even offline.
- New deps: @vue-flow/core (^1.48) + @dagrejs/dagre (^1.1, the maintained dagre fork). Vue Flow custom node registered via the `#node-lineage` slot; layout in views/lineage/layout.ts (dagre TB, node 320x68).
- lineageScope Pinia store is persisted; setSspId() clears componentId (a component belongs to an SSP). setTypes([]) falls back to all types (never an empty filter).
- Nav entry "Lineage" is intentionally ungated (no permission) for the PoC.
